Malaysia Stock Movers: Bumi Armada, CIMB, DRB, Genting, RHB, UEM

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n   a n d   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-08-26T09:13:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/malaysia-stock-movers-bumi-armada-cimb-drb-genting-rhb-uem.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. trading close in
 Kuala Lumpur .  Malaysia’s  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 19.93, or
1.4 percent, to 1,444.81, its lowest close since Sept. 9, 2010.  Financial Stocks:  CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB)  ,
Malaysia’s second-biggest banking group, dropped 2.9 percent to
7.04 ringgit, its lowest close since July 7, 2010. Investors are
reducing holdings in cyclical stocks including banks, said Lye
Thim Loong, a  fund manager  at Avenue Invest Bhd.  RHB Capital
Bhd. (RHBC)   fell 2.6 percent to 8.10 ringgit, while  Hong
Leong Financial Group Bhd. (HLFG)   declined 3.8 percent to
11.68 ringgit.       Bumi Armada Bhd. (BAB MK), a Malaysian oil and gas services
company, tumbled 7.1 percent to 3.53 ringgit, its lowest close
since its July 21 listing debut, after net income fell 18
percent to 60.3 million ringgit ($20 million).  DRB-Hicom Bhd. (DRB)  , an automotive, construction and
banking group, lost 2.9 percent to 2.01 ringgit, the lowest
close since July 25, after it reported a 42 percent decline in
first-quarter profit to 91.1 million ringgit.        Genting Bhd. (GENT)  , a casino, power and plantation
group, slid 3.3 percent to 9.46 ringgit, the lowest since Sept.
9, after second-quarter profit fell 9 percent to 673.2 million
ringgit, dragged down by lower takings at its Singapore gaming
resort.        Lion Diversified Holdings Bhd. (LDHB)  , a steel products
manufacturer, fell 3.8 percent to 38 sen, its lowest close since
June 21, after fourth-quarter earnings tumbled 92 percent. Lion
Corp. (LION MK), its subsidiary, dropped 4.3 percent to 22.5 sen
after reporting a fourth-quarter loss of 45.1 million ringgit.        UEM Land Holdings Bhd. (ULHB)  , a developer, fell 2.4
percent to 2.05 ringgit, the lowest level since Sept. 28, 2010.
The stock was downgraded by brokerages including RHB Research
Institute Sdn., which said in a report that the company’s
quarterly earnings missed expectations and projects may slow.  To contact the reporters on this story:
